4400.name: White Fabric
4400.description: A large piece of white cloth given by Magister Hanellin. Hanellin will tell you its purpose.

4401.name: Green Dimensional Stone
4401.description: Activates a Dimensional Vortex. Allows you to move to the 1st to 3rd floor of the Tower of Insolence. H5 Price

4402.name: Blue Dimensional Stone
4402.description: Activates a Dimensional Vortex. Allows you to move to the 4th to 6th floor of the Tower of Insolence. H5 Price

4403.name: Red Dimensional Stone
4403.description: Activates a Dimensional Vortex. Allows you to move to the 7th to 10th floor of the Tower of Insolence. H5 Price

4404.name: Green Dimensional Stone - Shard
4404.description: A broken shard of the green Dimensional Stone. Collect these and take them to Researcher Kaplan.

4405.name: Blue Dimensional Stone - Shard
4405.description: A broken shard of the blue Dimensional Stone. Collect these and take them to Researcher Euclie.

4406.name: Red Dimensional Stone - Shard
4406.description: A broken shard of the red Dimensional Stone. Collect these and take them to Researcher Pitagon.

4407.name: Bill of Iason Heine
4407.description: Its value is 1000 adena, redeemable by Roman of the Blacksmith Guild in Innadril. You can use it to buy various ingredients.

4408.name: Musical Score - Theme of Love
4408.description: Posthumously released musical score of Gillian. If you take it to Maestro Melody, you can have an echo crystal made.

4409.name: Musical Score - Theme of Battle
4409.description: The musical score for the Battle March of Flames. If you take it to Maestro Melody, you can have an echo crystal made.

4410.name: Musical Score - Theme of Journey
4410.description: A musical score composed by Troubadour Swan. If you take it to Maestro Melody, you can have an echo crystal made.

4411.name: Echo Crystal - Theme of Journey
4411.description: An echo crystal that plays the theme music of a journey. May only be used once. Item - Race Sound Crystal

4412.name: Echo Crystal - Theme of Battle
4412.description: An echo crystal that plays the theme music of a battle. Item - Race Sound Crystal

4413.name: Echo Crystal - Theme of Love
4413.description: An echo crystal that plays the theme music of love. May only be used once. Item - Race Sound Crystal

4414.name: Echo Crystal - Theme of Solitude
4414.description: An echo crystal that plays the theme music of solitude. May only be used once. Item - Race Sound Crystal

4415.name: Echo Crystal - Theme of the Feast
4415.description: An echo crystal that plays the theme music of a feast. May only be used once. Item - Race Sound Crystal

4416.name: Echo Crystal - Theme of Celebration
4416.description: An echo crystal that plays the theme music of a celebration. May only be used once. Item - Theme Sound Crystal

4417.name: Echo Crystal - Theme of Comedy
4417.description: An echo crystal that plays the theme music of a comedy. May only be used once. Item - Theme Sound Crystal

4418.name: Musical Score - Theme of Celebration
4418.description: A musical score containing the theme music of a celebration. If you take it to Maestro Melody, you can have an echo crystal made.

4419.name: Musical Score - Theme of Comedy
4419.description: A musical score containing the theme music of a comedy. If you take it to Maestro Melody, you can have an echo crystal made.

4420.name: Musical Score - Theme of Solitude
4420.description: A musical score composed by Musician Nanarin. If you take it to Maestro Melody, you can have an echo crystal made.

4421.name: Musical Score - Theme of the Feast
4421.description: A musical score composed by Musician Barbado. If you take it to Maestro Melody, you can have an echo crystal made.

4422.name: Dragon Bugle of Wind
4422.description: A bugle used to summon a Wind Strider. This pet uses some of the experience points earned by its master. Wolf's Necklace

4423.name: Dragon Bugle of Star
4423.description: A bugle used to summon a Star Strider. This pet uses some of the experience points earned by its master. Wolf's Necklace

4424.name: Dragon Bugle of Twilight
4424.description: A bugle used to summon a Twilight Strider. This pet uses some of the experience points earned by its master. Wolf's Necklace

4425.name: Penitent's Manacles
4425.description: The heavy manacles used to summon a Sin Eater. Summoning the Sin Eater consumes all the summoner's Exp. The Sin Eater must be fed Food for Wolves. Wolf's Necklace

4426.name: Manacles of Penitent
4426.description: Having consumed your sins, the Sin Eater has disappeared, leaving you with this ordinary pair of manacles. To repeat this quest, take them back to the Black Judge.

4427.name: Alligator Leather Belt
4427.description: An Alligator Leather Belt designed and created by Verche, a master leather craftsman.

4428.name: Blue Alligator Leather Belt
4428.description: An Alligator Leather Belt designed and created by Verche, a master leather craftsman. It is made from a rare blue type of Leather.

4429.name: Bejeweled Leather Belt
4429.description: An Alligator Leather Belt designed and created by Verche, a master leather craftsman. It is made from a Leather that is studded with rare jewels.

4430.name: Alligator Leather Purse
4430.description: An Alligator Leather Purse designed and created by Verche, a master leather craftsman.

4431.name: Blue Alligator Leather Purse
4431.description: An Alligator Leather Purse designed and created by Verche, a master leather craftsman. It is made from a rare blue type of Leather.

4432.name: Bejeweled Purse
4432.description: An Alligator Leather Purse designed and created by Verche, a master leather craftsman. It is made of Leather studded with rare jewels.

4433.name: Elemental Stone Powder
4433.description: Elemental stone powder obtained from a stone statue in the Forgotten Temple. Can be sold at any store or taken to Magister Nell.

4434.name: Elemental Stone Shards
4434.description: The shards of elemental stones obtained from stone statues in the Forgotten Temple. Can be sold at any store or taken to Magister Nell.

4435.name: Elemental Stone Lump
4435.description: The lumps of elemental stone obtained from stone statues in the Forgotten Temple. Can be sold at any store or taken to Magister Nell.

4436.name: Bentley's Request
4436.description: A request to find and bring back jade crystals from creatures such as Fline, Liele, Satyr etc. that inhabit the Enchanted Valley.

4437.name: Carson's Request
4437.description: A request to recover the works of the ancient sculptor Berona from Hatar Ratmen and Vanor Silenos in the area near the Cemetery.

4438.name: Knuckle Duster Edge
4438.description: An essential ingredient needed by a Dwarf to make a Knuckle Duster. It can be bought from a regular store.

4439.name: Avadon Shield Fragment
4439.description: An essential ingredient needed by a Dwarf to make an Avadon Shield. It can be bought from a regular store.

4440.name: Recipe: Knuckle Duster
4440.description: For Dwarves only. The recipe for a Knuckle Duster. Requires Create Item - Skill Level 5. The success rate is 100%.

4441.name: Recipe: Avadon Shield
4441.description: For Dwarves only. The recipe for an Avadon Shield. Requires Create Item - Skill Level 6. The success rate is 100%.

4442.name: Lottery Ticket
4442.description: A lottery ticket from Aden, redeemable at any lottery sales location. Winning numbers are posted every Saturday at 7 p.m. You can't win if you don't play! Good luck!

4443.name: Monster Race Ticket - Single
4443.description: A winning ticket from the monster race. Redeemable at the cashier of the race.

4444.name: Monster Race Ticket - Double
4444.description: A winning daily double ticket from the monster race. Redeemable at the cashier of the race.
